article.headline: Hampton 70, N. Carolina A&T 64
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Matthew Pilgrim scored 24 points in Hampton's 70-64 victory over North Carolina A&T on Monday. Rashad West scored 15 points and Demario Mattox added 13 for the Pirates (8-12, 4-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who led 41-30 at the half. Hampton held the Aggies to 33.3 percent shooting. Steven Rush scored a game-high 28 points for North Carolina A&T, while Jason Wills added 12 points and went 10-for-15 from the free throw line. Pilgrim hit 3-for-4 on 3-pointers while Mattox hit 3-of-7 from behind the arc.
